    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nnvim relies on file checksums to determine undo history. Consequently, when a file is modified by another tool, the checksum validation fails, causing the undo history to be cleared.\n\nThis functionality causes nvim's undo history to be constantly wiped when collaborating with other tools (such as IDEs or Agents), making the undo feature invalid.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen a file is modified by other tools, nvim's undo should restore the file to the last version it remembered, rather than resetting the undo history. This allows for continuous tracking of the undo history.\n\nConsider refactoring the existing plugin (https://github.com/kevinhwang91/nvim-fundo) and providing this functionality as a built-in plugin.",
